table-0636-975.caption: Confirmed tornadoes
data: Tornado crossed from Georgia into South Carolina near Toccoa. A shopping plaza was severely damaged, and a drugstore and a supermarket sustained major structural damage. Homes and mobile homes were damaged as well, and downed power lines started a house fire. $2.9 million in damage.

2 Deaths - First violent tornado of the outbreak passed close to Chesnee before crossing the NC/SC state line into SE Rutherford County. Homes were leveled and swept away near Chesnee, and two people were killed in that area. Near Henrietta, three trailers, one business, and four homes were destroyed, one of which was a well-built brick home. Six trailers and 21 homes were damaged. Caused $3,500,000 in damage and injured 35 people.

Tornado moved through southern and eastern Durham. Two businesses were destroyed, and a convenience store was nearly destroyed. 16 homes were destroyed and 46 others were damaged. An elementary school was damaged as well. Caused $15,000,000 in damage, but no fatalities or injuries occurred.
Tornado was spawned by the Durham supercell.
Struck the Winston-Salem suburb of Clemmons. A gas station was destroyed, trees were downed, and homes were damaged. Three people were injured.
A trailer, a house, and several barns were destroyed. 5 other residences were damaged, and one person was injured.
Very brief touchdown, from the same storm that produced the earlier Indian Trail tornado.

Third Forsyth County tornado, formed almost immediately after the Winston-Salem tornado dissipated, and continued along an extension of the same path. 30 aircraft at Smith-Reynolds Airport were tossed and hangars were damaged.
Tornado produced F1 damage in western Burlington and Elon.
Isolated tornado touches down between Charlottesville and Richmond. F1 damage occurred along a short, but wide path.
Second Louisa County tornado touches down from separate thunderstorm, several miles east of previous Louisa tornado.

The Bugaloos come to Sparky's aid after he takes the fall for Benita's act of radio-station sabotage.
Benita pumps smog into Tranquility Forest in an effort to drive the audience away from a Bugaloos concert and over to her own.
Sparky finally learns to fly, and he quickly puts his skills to good use, rescuing the Bugaloos after they are shrunk and trapped inside a music box.
Disguised as an agent, Benita tricks Sparky into writing a song for her to perform at Peter Platter's "Battle of the Bands" concert.
Benita kidnaps Peter Platter and takes over as DJ. But I.Q. disguises himself as Benita in an effort to foil her scheme.
Benita interferes with the Bugaloos' plan to hold a circus by kidnapping Magico the Magnificent.
Used-car dealer Way Out Wheeler stages an auto race, pitting the Bugaloos against Benita. The stakes are raised, however, when she kidnaps Sparky and threatens to harm him if the Bugaloos win.
Benita buys Tranquility Forest and evicts the Bugaloos. But Joy, disguised as a fortune teller, tries to show Benita the error of her ways through a series of clips from previous episodes.

table-0636-597.caption: Forecast
data: Tornado destroyed 19 trailers and damaged 13 others. Five community buildings were destroyed, along with 500 acres of timber. 43 people were injured.

1 death - Large F2 tornado moved NE through downtown Newberry, which reportedly resembled a "war zone" after the tornado struck. 80 businesses were damaged or destroyed. A church lost its roof and a wall, and a dance academy building partially collapsed. The path of this storm was 3/4 of a mile in width in places. Caused $11,000,000 in damage and injured 38 people. Fatality occurred when an automotive shop was destroyed.

Intense tornado touched down just east of downtown Newberry, and moved to the east. The two Newberry tornadoes destroyed 254 houses, 86 businesses, 45 trailers, 68 farm buildings, 7 large public buildings, and generated a total of $14,200,000 in damage. This second tornado injured 10 people.
Massive timber damage was reported S of Kershaw, and a mobile home park was destroyed. 31 people were injured.
Tornado touched down in the Sandhills National Wildlife Refuge, leveling pine forests.
Four homes and two businesses were destroyed in town. 36 farm buildings were destroyed in and near town, and large swaths of forest were leveled. 24 people were injured.
Tornado touched down NW of Conway, and was isolated from other tornado families in this outbreak. Two trailers were destroyed in South Carolina, injuring eight people.
F2 damage occurred in West Mount.
Tornado passed along the SE edge of LaGrange, destroying several homes and injuring 81 people.

6 Deaths - In the NW corner of Bertie County, the tornado circulation was up to 1/-mile (km) wide. Deaths were at a trailer park in the path of the storm, where a family of 5 was killed. Caused $5,000,000 in damage and 19 injuries.
Caused F2 damage and 7 injuries near Ahoskie.
Caused damage near Harrellsville and the Wiccacon River.
